Sorry, trouble concentrating.

28
00:02:53,549 --> 00:02:55,883
That tank top
really absorbs moisture.

29
00:02:57,511 --> 00:02:59,846
Could impinge the ulnar nerve,
cut the blood flow.

30
00:02:59,972 --> 00:03:03,140
Or it could be disseminated
intravascular coagulopathy.

31
00:03:03,267 --> 00:03:04,559
DIC?

32
00:03:04,685 --> 00:03:06,686
Guy falls off a roof,
the first thought is always,

33
00:03:06,812 --> 00:03:07,852
"It's a clotting problem".

34
00:03:07,938 --> 00:03:10,439
Trauma can activate
the clotting enzymes.

35
00:03:10,566 --> 00:03:13,401
- Guy could lose more than his hand.
- Thank you very much.

36
00:03:13,527 --> 00:03:15,486
This guy's been working for me
for a long time, and I...

37
00:03:15,612 --> 00:03:18,281
Do I get bonus points
if I act like I care?

38
00:03:19,867 --> 00:03:23,828
Cervical MRI. Work up for DIC.
And start him on a heparin drip.

39
00:03:23,954 --> 00:03:25,413
- Who?
- You wanna know his name?

40
00:03:25,539 --> 00:03:28,082
I'm sure it's in the file.
Or you could ask her.

41
00:03:28,208 --> 00:03:31,043
She's his oldest, bestest friend.
They were in Cub Scouts together.

42
00:03:31,169 --> 00:03:32,795
I'll get started
on the blood tests.

43
00:03:32,921 --> 00:03:34,839
You haven't been
a real doctor in 10 years.

44
00:03:34,965 --> 00:03:36,526
You'll make a mess all over the sheets.

45
00:03:36,550 --> 00:03:38,426
- I'll do it.
- You have clinic duty.

46
00:03:38,552 --> 00:03:41,137
- I still know how to handle a patient.
- Get me blood.

47
00:03:41,263 --> 00:03:42,930
Lots of blood.

48
00:03:43,056 --> 00:03:44,974
They're better.
They've showered.

49
00:04:01,658 --> 00:04:03,576
You don't need to see him.

50
00:04:03,702 --> 00:04:06,746
One-handed handymen
aren't in big demand.

51
00:04:06,872 --> 00:04:09,582
Talking. That's how
lawsuits are lost.

52
00:04:09,708 --> 00:04:10,791
I know you, Lisa.

53
00:04:10,918 --> 00:04:13,836
You go in, you offer
to pay his medical bills, his wages,

54
