like, "I'm sorry".

55
00:04:15,756 --> 00:04:16,881
You think I'm an idiot.

56
00:04:17,007 --> 00:04:19,717
I think you're not a lawyer.
Don't go in there.

57
00:04:21,303 --> 00:04:23,638
Trust me, House's people
can handle this.

58
00:04:25,724 --> 00:04:26,891
Yeah.

59
00:04:28,352 --> 00:04:30,269
This might sting a little bit.

60
00:04:30,896 --> 00:04:34,023
The medicine will thin the blood
and help it to circulate.

61
00:04:34,149 --> 00:04:36,067
Those are pretty
nasty scars there.

62
00:04:36,944 --> 00:04:38,527
I work construction.

63
00:04:43,200 --> 00:04:44,909
How long
will I be in the hospital?

64
00:04:45,035 --> 00:04:47,411
Depends how long it takes us
to figure out what's going on.

65
00:04:47,537 --> 00:04:49,372
I need to work. I'll get fired.

66
00:04:49,498 --> 00:04:51,040
I'm sure Dr. Cuddy
won't fire you.

67
00:04:51,166 --> 00:04:53,751
I'm a janitor at fast food six nights.
I need to work.

68
00:04:53,877 --> 00:04:56,317
- My mother doesn't make enough.
- I can work. I'm old enough.

69
00:04:56,421 --> 00:04:58,061
You're old enough
when you finish college.

70
00:04:58,131 --> 00:04:59,131
Why? You never went...

71
00:04:59,257 --> 00:05:01,137
I never had a big brother
to tell me to shut up!

72
00:05:01,176 --> 00:05:04,428
I promise we'll let you out of
here as soon as we're able to.

73
00:05:04,554 --> 00:05:08,432
Look, I... I am fine. Okay?
I feel better. I go home now.

74
00:05:08,558 --> 00:05:11,560
No. If this is a clotting problem,
it could be very serious.

75
00:05:11,687 --> 00:05:13,437
- All right?
- Look, you can't make me stay.

76
00:05:13,563 --> 00:05:15,898
- Wait...
- You can't make me stay.

77
00:05:16,024 --> 00:05:17,566
Turn your hand over.

78
00:05:18,276 --> 00:05:19,902
I need to see your hand.

79
00:05:25,909 --> 00:05:27,118
Where's Dr. Cuddy?

80
00:05:27,369 --> 00:05:29,036
We've got a third finger
turning dark.

81
00:05:29,162 --> 00:05:32,248
His PTT is prolonged and the fibrin
split products are off.

82
00:05:32,374 --> 00:05:35,251
He's not clotting properly.
It looks like a mild case of DIC.

83
00:05:35,377 --> 00:05:36,919
Well, obviously not that mild.

84
00:05:37,045 --> 00:05:39,463
This keeps up, his hand is
literally gonna be dead meat.

85
00:05:39,589 --> 00:05:42,717
His hand is connected to his arm,
and his arm is connected to...

86
00:05:42,843 --> 00:05:44,363
I'm not sure,
but I bet it's important.

87
00:05:44,386 --> 00:05:46,554
All this from falling off
my roof!

88
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:49,473
Yeah. If only he'd fallen
on his head.

89
00:05:49,599 --> 00:05:52,268
Then he wouldn't have any
of these symptoms.

90
00:05:53,311 --> 00:05:55,563
We need something
stronger than heparin.

91
00:05:57,232 --> 00:05:59,191
Human Activated Protein C.

92
00:05:59,317 --> 00:06:01,569
Looks like Cuddy,
same cleavage.

93
00:06:02,237 --> 00:06:05,281
Protein C is indicated
only for severe sepsis.

94
00:06:05,407 --> 00:06:07,867
How many of his limbs have to be
at stake for it to be severe?

95
00:06:07,993 --> 00:06:10,619
But this stuff
is crazy dangerous.

96
00:06:10,746 --> 00:06:12,204
It can cause internal bleeding.

97
00:06:12,330 --> 00:06:13,581
If he bleeds, he could stroke,
he could die.

98
00:06:13,707 --> 00:06:14,874
He could get better.

99
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:16,959
You know, if I try
to scheme like this,

100
00:06:17,085 --> 00:06:20,254
you get that nasty wrinkly
face and screech like a hyena.

101
00:06:20,380 --> 00:06:22,089
It's very sexy, I admit.

102
00:06:23,842 --> 00:06:24,842
Do it.

103
00:06:29,014 --> 00:06:31,932
Protein C
is borderline irresponsible,

104
00:06:32,059 --> 00:06:34,101
except that the safe stuff
isn't doing squat.

105
00:06:34,227 --> 00:06:37,396
- It's exactly what you would do.
- Obviously.

106
00:06:38,398 --> 00:06:41,317
- It's exactly what he'd do.
- I know.

107
00:06:41,443 --> 00:06:43,486
I think he's trying
to protect me.

108
00:06:43,612 --> 00:06:46,072
Now, that's not
the type of thing he would do.

109
00:06:46,198 --> 00:06:47,281
I overruled him.

110
00:06:47,407 --> 00:06:51,410
He's the best diagnostician in
this hospital, and I overrule him.

111
00:06:52,412 --> 00:06:53,913
You care about this kid.

112
00:06:54,039 --> 00:06:56,290
Your judgment
should be worth more than his.

113
00:06:56,416 --> 00:07:00,169
He also pointed out that I haven't
been a real doctor in years.

114
00:07:00,295 --> 00:07:02,213
Now that sounds like him.

115
00:07:02,339 --> 00:07:04,006
You were
just jerking Cuddy around?

116
00:07:04,132 --> 00:07:06,592
She seriously thought
I wanted to stop her.

117
00:07:06,718 --> 00:07:09,261
- One thing Cuddy is not is clueless.
- No.

118
00:07:09,387 --> 00:07:12,306
First casualty of this case
is her sense of humor.

119
00:07:12,432 --> 00:07:16,102
That's weird. There's nothing
funnier than almost killing a guy.

120
00:07:18,897 --> 00:07:21,315
I'm just having trouble
getting up those steps.

121
00:07:21,441 --> 00:07:24,276
- When did you start noticing?
- Oh, a week ago.

122
00:07:24,402 --> 00:07:26,278
Your blood pressure's
a little high.

123
00:07:26,404 --> 00:07:28,284
I've got something new
that should help you out.

124
00:07:28,406 --> 00:07:30,741
It combines a nitrate
with a blood pressure pill.

125
00:07:30,867 --> 00:07:33,285
It's targeted
to African-Americans.

126
00:07:33,411 --> 00:07:34,662
Targeted?

127
00:07:34,788 --> 00:07:37,498
Yeah. Well, see, we tend to
have nitric oxide deficiencies.

128
00:07:37,624 --> 00:07:39,785
And the studies show this drug
counteracts that problem.

129
00:07:39,793 --> 00:07:40,626
It's the first drug to...

130
00:07:40,752 --> 00:07:42,878
What kind of studies you talking about?

131
00:07:43,004 --> 00:07:44,588
What kind of studies are there?

132
00:07:44,714 --> 00:07:47,508
They get some patients.
They give them some drugs.

133
00:07:48,760 --> 00:07:51,387
I've had white people
lying to me for 60 years.

134
00:07:52,389 --> 00:07:55,891
- You think this is a tan?
- You think they tell you everything?

135
00:07:57,102 --> 00:07:58,342
The trouble with us black folk,

136
00:07:58,395 --> 00:08:01,105
we can't tell the difference
anymore between racism

137
00:08:01,231 --> 00:08:03,357
- and everybody gets screwed.
- Yeah?

138
00:08:03,483 --> 00:08:07,319
Well, how about them cheap meningitis
drugs they're pawning off in Africa?

139
00:08:07,445 --> 00:08:10,698
- Gonna tell me that ain't racism?
- That's just greed.

140
00:08:12,659 --> 00:08:14,285
You really wanna screw whitey?

141
00:08:14,411 --> 00:08:18,706
Be one of the few black men who live
long enough to collect social security.

142
00:08:18,832 --> 00:08:20,332
Take the medicine.

143
00:08:34,806 --> 00:08:36,265
Nurse.

144
00:08:36,391 --> 00:08:39,560
Nurse! Help! Nurse! Help!

145
00:08:40,395 --> 00:08:41,478
- Nurse!
- What's up?

146
00:08:41,605 --> 00:08:45,441
- I can't move my arm!
- Take it easy. Take it easy.

147
00:08:48,862 --> 00:08:52,948
The Protein C side effects we were
worried about, they happened.

148
00:08:53,074 --> 00:08:54,867
- Where was the bleed?
- His brain.

149
00:08:54,993 --> 00:08:56,452
It's causing
right side paralysis.

150
00:08:56,578 --> 00:08:59,622
I've stopped the treatment
and called a neurosurgeon.

151
00:09:39,079 --> 00:09:40,579
I can move it now.

152
00:09:40,705 --> 00:09:43,540
- It's okay now? Can I go home soon?
- The surgery went well.

153
00:09:43,667 --> 00:09:46,752
But all we did was fix the problem
created by the medicine we gave you.

154
00:09:50,548 --> 00:09:52,424
She says you... You look young.

155
00:09:53,051 --> 00:09:54,093
Are you sure...

156
00:09:54,219 --> 00:09:56,553
There's five of us working on the case.

157
00:09:56,680 --> 00:09:58,639
The others are older.

158
00:09:58,765 --> 00:10:00,808
Why doesn't Dr. Cuddy
come to...

159
00:10:05,939 --> 00:10:07,731
That doesn't sound too good.

160
00:10:19,953 --> 00:10:21,328
His fingers are even darker.

161
00:10:21,454 --> 00:10:23,247
His temperature's 102
and spiking.

162
00:10:23,373 --> 00:10:27,042
And the x-ray
now shows lung infiltrates.

163
00:10:27,168 --> 00:10:30,921
Well, the good news is he won't be bitching
about losing his hand if he can't breathe.

164
00:10:31,047 --> 00:10:34,300
The trauma from the fall could have caused
acute respiratory distress syndrome.

165
00:10:34,426 --> 00:10:36,260
Right. I forgot. Your roof.

166
00:10:36,386 --> 00:10:39,179
It would cause lung
infiltrates and maybe fever

167
00:10:39,306 --> 00:10:41,181
and conceivably
the cyanotic fingers.

168
00:10:41,308 --> 00:10:44,476
- The only question is why.
- Why what?

169
00:10:44,769 --> 00:10:46,603
Why her weird psychopathology

170
00:10:46,730 --> 00:10:50,774
requires a diagnosis informed
entirely by personal guilt.

171
00:10:50,900 --> 00:10:53,235
Let's assume
we've been wrong up until now.

172
00:10:53,361 --> 00:10:55,070
Let's assume,
just for one second,

173
00:10:55,196 --> 00:10:58,032
that the earth doesn't revolve
around Cuddy's roof.

174
00:10:58,825 --> 00:11:02,161
What if he was sick before he
had his run-in with gravity?

175
00:11:02,287 --> 00:11:03,487
He just didn't notice anything.

176
00:11:03,496 --> 00:11:06,373
Well, pneumonia can cause DIC
which can cause cyanotic fingers.

177
00:11:06,499 --> 00:11:08,542
- Pneumonia doesn't hit that fast.
- Sure.

178
00:11:08,668 --> 00:11:12,129
Only pavement hits that fast.
It's not pneumonia.

179
00:11:12,922 --> 00:11:14,602
He might have missed
a finger turning dark.

180
00:11:14,674 --> 00:11:16,194
He's not gonna miss
breathing problems.

181
00:11:16,259 --> 00:11:18,010
- What else?
- It's pneumonia.

182
00:11:20,305 --> 00:11:22,264
He wanted to go home.
I thought he was lying.

183
00:11:22,390 --> 00:11:25,476
I told him I had a dinner party.
I made him go up there.

184
00:11:26,227 --> 00:11:28,388
Well, why didn't you just
take out a gun and shoot him?

185
00:11:28,480 --> 00:11:30,147
I thought it was just asthma.

186
00:11:30,273 --> 00:11:32,358
You might've mentioned this
earlier, Doctor.

187
00:11:32,484 --> 00:11:35,069
Maybe we could have sent
some blood cultures to the lab

188
00:11:35,195 --> 00:11:37,696
instead of wasting a day
indulging your self-loathing.

189
00:11:37,822 --> 00:11:42,117
If it's just garden-variety bacterial
pneumonia, he's gonna be fine.

190
00:11:42,243 --> 00:11:45,621
So give him garden-variety Levaquin,
and a garden-variety echocardiogram.

191
00:11:45,747 --> 00:11:47,027
And go check out
the kid's house.

192
00:11:47,082 --> 00:11:49,442
The blood work will show us which
type of pneumonia it is...

193
00:11:49,459 --> 00:11:52,961
If he's huffing nail polish or pulling
the wings off his pet parrot,

194
00:11:53,088 --> 00:11:54,380
this way'll be faster.

195
00:11:54,506 --> 00:11:57,674
And I bet Julio's just dying to
find out what's wrong with him.

196
00:11:57,801 --> 00:12:00,177
- Go with her.
- It's Alfredo.

197
00:12:01,054 --> 00:12:02,846
And I can handle
getting a key and...

198
00:12:02,972 --> 00:12:06,892
Rico and I no longer trust you deciding
what's important and what's not.

199
00:12:13,900 --> 00:12:17,152
You ever think about writing
a book on office politics?

200
00:12:17,278 --> 00:12:18,487
Trust me,

201
00:12:18,613 --> 00:12:21,907
it would be a lot worse if I told her
that you had to break into her house.

202
00:12:22,909 --> 00:12:26,120
What? Wait, wait, wait...
Cuddy's house?

203
00:12:26,246 --> 00:12:27,830
See? It is shocking.

204
00:12:28,832 --> 00:12:31,352
The guy's been working there every
day for the last three weeks.

205
00:12:31,459 --> 00:12:33,335
You think it's impossible he
could've picked something up?

206
00:12:33,461 --> 00:12:36,630
- I'm not breaking into my boss's house.
- I'm your boss.

207
00:12:36,756 --> 00:12:38,507
She's scarier than you are.

208
00:12:39,134 --> 00:12:42,469
She's a woman.
Relax. I'm coming with.

209
00:12:48,435 --> 00:12:50,978
House is having lunch
with his juniors now?

210
00:12:51,104 --> 00:12:53,730
- No. Not a chance.
- Then where do you think they're going?

211
00:12:53,857 --> 00:12:56,150
I have no idea.

212
00:12:56,276 --> 00:12:57,693
Then why don't you think
they're going to lunch?

213
00:12:57,819 --> 00:13:00,020
Because it's not like House.
That was your point, right?

214
00:13:00,029 --> 00:13:01,350
He had that smug look
on his face.

215
00:13:01,448 --> 00:13:02,656
When he's that pleased
about something

216
00:13:02,782 --> 00:13:05,302
he's gotta tell somebody, and the
only somebody he knows is you.

217
00:13:06,870 --> 00:13:10,456
- He's breaking into Cuddy's home.
- What?

218
00:13:10,582 --> 00:13:11,623
Why?

219
00:13:12,542 --> 00:13:14,251
Medical reasons?

220
00:13:14,377 --> 00:13:15,836
Why is he so curious
about Cuddy?

221
00:13:15,962 --> 00:13:17,337
Why are you so curious
about his curiosity?

222
00:13:17,464 --> 00:13:18,785
Why are you so curious
about me...

223
00:13:18,798 --> 00:13:21,341
Because you dumped him
and you're married

224
00:13:21,468 --> 00:13:25,012
and they are neither
of those things.

225
00:13:25,138 --> 00:13:26,472
I'm just curious.

226
00:13:27,390 --> 00:13:30,476
- Nothing wrong with that.
- No. Nothing wrong with that.

227
00:13:34,689 --> 00:13:36,648
What do you think? Red thongs?

228
00:13:38,067 --> 00:13:39,776
I think red thongs.

229
00:13:41,196 --> 00:13:44,948
Okay, 20 bucks says I can get
through this door in 20 seconds.

230
00:13:45,074 --> 00:13:46,700
- You're on.
- Count me in.

231
00:14:03,384 --> 00:14:07,429
No furniture polish, no paint thinner,
nor anything else worth sniffing.

232
00:14:07,555 --> 00:14:11,391
Nothing in here, either,
except a few cockroaches.

233
00:14:12,685 --> 00:14:16,146
Nice. Someone
should fix Alfredo's roof.

234
00:14:18,358 --> 00:14:21,652
So, why haven't you
fired House?

235
00:14:23,613 --> 00:14:26,949
It's just, you guys are always
screaming at each other,

236
00:14:27,075 --> 00:14:29,743
- and I figure you hate him, so...
- I don't hate him.

237
00:14:32,121 --> 00:14:33,121
Why not?

238
00:14:35,250 --> 00:14:37,167
