00:29:10,207 --> 00:29:13,042
I gave one of my clinic
patients a follow-up call.

483
00:29:13,168 --> 00:29:14,919
Your name came up.

484
00:29:16,004 --> 00:29:17,880
I'm guessing an old black guy

485
00:29:18,006 --> 00:29:21,676
who thinks the CIA invented rap music to
make your people want to kill each other.

486
00:29:21,802 --> 00:29:24,220
He said you gave him
the white folks' stuff.

487
00:29:24,972 --> 00:29:27,092
This is exactly why black
people don't live as long...

488
00:29:27,141 --> 00:29:30,810
This isn't about race,
unless annoying is a race.

489
00:29:30,936 --> 00:29:33,396
- Is he not getting better?
- He's fine so far.

490
00:29:34,481 --> 00:29:37,525
I'm calling him back in. I'm
getting him on the right stuff.

491
00:29:37,651 --> 00:29:39,986
Relax, Foreman, he already is.

492
00:29:41,989 --> 00:29:45,408
I told him it was the white stuff.
I gave him the black stuff.

493
00:29:48,996 --> 00:29:50,079
He was right.

494
00:29:51,081 --> 00:29:52,748
You did exactly
what white people do.

495
00:29:52,875 --> 00:29:55,960
You figure we don't need to know
the truth or can't understand it,

496
00:29:56,086 --> 00:29:58,296
so you just lie to us.

497
00:29:58,422 --> 00:30:01,007
- Just a white lie.
- Good one, massa.

498
00:30:02,009 --> 00:30:03,509
Right, and I'm a racist.

499
00:30:05,012 --> 00:30:08,973
Too bad that idiot will never know
for the rest of his long, long life.

500
00:30:15,981 --> 00:30:20,526
Every slave master thought they
were doing the black man a favor.

501
00:30:21,320 --> 00:30:25,114
Negro can't take care of himself,
so we'll put him to work.

502
00:30:25,991 --> 00:30:27,950
We'll give him four walls,
a bed.

503
00:30:29,620 --> 00:30:31,370
We'll civilize the heathen.

504
00:30:31,497 --> 00:30:33,998
I'll tell you what.
Stop doing us favors.

505
00:30:35,000 --> 00:30:37,293
If you're right, and we end up
back in the jungle

506
00:30:37,419 --> 00:30:39,629
with lousy
blood pressure medicine,

507
00:30:40,297 --> 00:30:42,006
it won't be on your head.

508
00:31:35,352 --> 00:31:36,352
You okay?

509
00:31:39,940 --> 00:31:42,233
You wondering
if you made the right call?

510
00:31:44,194 --> 00:31:46,988
I've wanted to be a doctor
from the time I was 12.

511
00:31:48,991 --> 00:31:50,866
I wanted to be a lawyer
from the time I was six

512
00:31:50,993 --> 00:31:52,952
until my second week
of law school.

513
00:31:53,078 --> 00:31:54,704
Sorry. Your story.

514
00:31:56,999 --> 00:32:01,085
I graduated medical school at 25, pissed
off that I was second in my class.

515
00:32:02,004 --> 00:32:06,632
Chief of medicine at 32, second
youngest ever, first woman...

516
00:32:06,758 --> 00:32:07,758
Sad story.

517
00:32:07,884 --> 00:32:09,885
If I had been
Alfredo's doctor...

518
00:32:10,012 --> 00:32:11,512
You are his doctor.

519
00:32:13,140 --> 00:32:16,809
I insisted on giving him Protein C.
We had to cut his skull open.

520
00:32:16,935 --> 00:32:20,187
I insisted on amphotericin,
killed his kidneys.

521
00:32:20,314 --> 00:32:22,481
I missed the pneumonia
completely.

522
00:32:23,358 --> 00:32:26,694
I would have searched his home
and ignored mine.

523
00:32:26,820 --> 00:32:30,781
I would have watched him die
trying to save his hand.

524
00:32:32,743 --> 00:32:35,911
If I didn't have House
looking over my shoulder...

525
00:32:36,038 --> 00:32:38,497
Are you saying you're not as
good a doctor as House is?

526
00:32:38,624 --> 00:32:40,249
I'm saying House is right.

527
00:32:42,002 --> 00:32:44,003
I was so anxious to get ahead.

528
00:32:45,005 --> 00:32:47,923
I haven't been a doctor
in years.

529
00:32:49,092 --> 00:32:51,093
His little finger is dusky.

530
00:32:51,219 --> 00:32:53,179
Yeah, that's why
we're doing this.

531
00:32:53,305 --> 00:32:57,016
No. I mean the other hand, the
one we haven't chopped off yet.

532
00:33:23,794 --> 00:33:25,795
His O2 sats are down to 88.

533
00:33:25,921 --> 00:33:28,631
His lungs are giving out.
He needs a ventilator.

534
00:33:29,466 --> 00:33:30,508
And dialysis.

535
00:33:30,634 --> 00:33:34,220
You're getting distracted by
the multisystem organ failure.

536
00:33:34,346 --> 00:33:37,056
Pinkies are supposed
to be pink, right?

537
00:33:37,182 --> 00:33:38,849
I mean,
they're not called "gray-ies".

538
00:33:38,975 --> 00:33:40,768
But the organ failure
is gonna kill him.

539
00:33:40,894 --> 00:33:42,645
But the pinky is weirder.

540
00:33:43,397 --> 00:33:44,522
What does it tell us?

541
00:33:44,648 --> 00:33:46,732
The same thing the right hand
told us before we cut it off.

542
00:33:46,858 --> 00:33:49,652
- It's the same symptom.
- But at a different time.

543
00:33:50,654 --> 00:33:53,239
His blood work
indicates mild DIC.

544
00:33:53,907 --> 00:33:56,867
What if it's mild in the way that
when you get out of the ocean,

545
00:33:56,993 --> 00:33:59,537
the water clinging to your
body makes the sea level drop?

546
00:33:59,663 --> 00:34:01,539
It's technically true, but
it's completely irrelevant.

547
00:34:01,665 --> 00:34:04,083
A lack of DIC
would explain everything

548
00:34:04,209 --> 00:34:06,961
if there were also
a lack of anything to explain.

549
00:34:09,339 --> 00:34:12,299
Endocarditis.
His heart's infected.

550
00:34:13,218 --> 00:34:16,721
Little bacteria cauliflowers,
clinging to his valves.

551
00:34:16,847 --> 00:34:20,224
Except sometimes they can't hold on.
They go swimming in his bloodstream.

552
00:34:20,350 --> 00:34:22,935
Thursday, one breaks off,
goes to his right hand,

553
00:34:23,061 --> 00:34:24,520
black fingers, gangrene.

554
00:34:24,646 --> 00:34:26,856
Friday's child
heads for the kidneys.

555
00:34:27,649 --> 00:34:30,151
And we all know
what Saturdays are all about.

556
00:34:30,277 --> 00:34:32,278
Party with the left hand.

557
00:34:32,404 --> 00:34:33,612
Also explains the fever.

558
00:34:33,739 --> 00:34:35,698
It's perfect
except for the little fact

559
00:34:35,824 --> 00:34:37,491
that we already tested
for endocarditis,

560
00:34:37,617 --> 00:34:38,534
and he was negative.

561
00:34:38,660 --> 00:34:41,287
Which means he either
is negative or...

562
00:34:41,413 --> 00:34:45,207
What infection can cause pneumonia
and culture-negative endocarditis?

563
00:34:47,544 --> 00:34:49,670
Prize value goes down
with every clue.

564
00:34:53,425 --> 00:34:55,259
You're thinking psittacosis?

565
00:34:55,385 --> 00:34:57,052
Alfredo doesn't have
any pet parrots.

566
00:34:57,179 --> 00:34:59,513
Quit your squawking.
Give him doxycycline.

567
00:34:59,639 --> 00:35:01,974
No! That'll just make
his clotting problem worse.

568
00:35:02,100 --> 00:35:05,519
I liked you better when you were coming
up with wacky drugs for us to try.

569
00:35:05,645 --> 00:35:09,064
We give him the doxy now, damn
it, maybe we can save his pinky.

570
00:35:09,191 --> 00:35:11,066
He can teach his brother
to count all the way to five.

571
00:35:11,193 --> 00:35:14,111
If you're wrong, he'll end up
with no hands and no feet.

572
00:35:14,237 --> 00:35:17,031
Technically, if I'm wrong, he'll end
up dead, but I take your point.

573
00:35:17,157 --> 00:35:19,637
- What's his night job?
- He cleans up at some fast food joint.

574
00:35:19,701 --> 00:35:21,581
What, you think he got it
from a chicken nugget?

575
00:35:21,661 --> 00:35:25,539
Since when do fast food joints
allow 12-year-olds to mop floors?

576
00:35:25,665 --> 00:35:28,751
- Alfredo is 20.
- Really? Looks younger.

577
00:35:32,464 --> 00:35:34,381
Where were you going
to work tonight?

578
00:35:34,508 --> 00:35:36,634
What job do you do
on Saturday nights?

579
00:35:39,346 --> 00:35:40,846
- What are you doing?
- Wake him up.

580
00:35:40,972 --> 00:35:42,515
We just cut off his hand.

581
00:35:42,641 --> 00:35:45,643
- Yeah. We need to talk about it.
- It's not happening.

582
00:35:52,067 --> 00:35:53,818
Honest, I've got no idea
what I just said.

583
00:35:53,944 --> 00:35:56,153
Why didn't you say
you spoke Spanish?

584
00:35:56,279 --> 00:35:58,489
Well, because
she'd wanna talk to me.

585
00:35:58,615 --> 00:36:00,533
Or something like that.

586
00:36:05,789 --> 00:36:07,540
She says he doesn't work
Saturday nights.

587
00:36:07,666 --> 00:36:08,833
Give me the talking juice.

588
00:36:08,959 --> 00:36:11,200
The fact it doesn't fit your
theory doesn't make it a lie.

589
00:36:11,211 --> 00:36:12,169
When she was out of the room,

590
00:36:12,295 --> 00:36:16,215
the kid brother insisted he was gonna
cover for Alfredo at work tonight.

591
00:36:23,598 --> 00:36:26,058
Saturday nights
he goes dancing.

592
00:36:26,184 --> 00:36:28,727
Either it's a lie
or he's dancing with birds.

593
00:36:30,647 --> 00:36:31,728
Give her the talking juice.

594
00:36:31,731 --> 00:36:33,524
She doesn't know
what you're talking about.

595
00:36:33,650 --> 00:36:35,067
Odds are it's gonna be
close to his house.

596
00:36:35,193 --> 00:36:37,528
It's probably an abandoned
warehouse or factory.

597
00:36:37,654 --> 00:36:39,822
Take the Scooby gang
and spread out.

598
00:36:39,948 --> 00:36:41,448
What the hell
are we looking for?

599
00:36:41,575 --> 00:36:43,242
Find somebody
who looks like crap.

600
00:36:43,368 --> 00:36:45,494
Tell him you want
to place a bet.

601
00:37:40,175 --> 00:37:41,342
It's Cuddy.

602
00:37:43,595 --> 00:37:45,971
I already put him
on the psittacosis meds.

603
00:37:46,973 --> 00:37:49,016
As soon as you left.

604
00:37:49,142 --> 00:37:50,517
You're welcome.

605
00:37:51,853 --> 00:37:54,980
What do you think the record
for one-handed juggling is?

606
00:37:55,899 --> 00:37:57,650
You can yo-yo one-handed.

607
00:37:58,652 --> 00:37:59,693
Good point.

608
00:38:08,411 --> 00:38:09,954
I always wash my hands.

609
00:38:10,956 --> 00:38:15,084
If a bird is infected, you can get
psittacosis just from breathing his dust.

610
00:38:15,919 --> 00:38:18,545
But then, why do I get sick
and nobody else?

611
00:38:18,672 --> 00:38:20,673
Your asthma
made you vulnerable.

612
00:38:24,135 --> 00:38:26,679
- You're gonna be all right now.
- Yes.

613
00:38:38,108 --> 00:38:39,608
For saving my life.

614
00:38:49,160 --> 00:38:50,828
He thanked me.

615
00:38:50,954 --> 00:38:53,497
- He should have.
- We cut off his hand.

616
00:38:56,501 --> 00:38:57,584
If we'd figured it out
earlier...

617
00:38:57,711 --> 00:38:59,586
If you'd figured it out later,
he'd be dead.

618
00:38:59,713 --> 00:39:01,880
I never figured it out at all.

619
00:39:02,966 --> 00:39:05,592
- Hello.
- What do you want, House?

620
00:39:06,302 --> 00:39:10,431
If you're wallowing in self-loathing,
I've got something that might help.

621
00:39:10,557 --> 00:39:11,890
We're getting sued.

622
00:39:12,559 --> 00:39:15,561
- You saved his life. He admitted that.
- We'll settle.

623
00:39:15,687 --> 00:39:18,605
He's got a stub where his hand
used to be. We have insurance.

624
00:39:18,732 --> 00:39:20,566
Case seems pretty solid to me.

625
00:39:21,526 --> 00:39:24,194
The new American dream.
Happy ending.

626
00:39:24,320 --> 00:39:26,155
Kid's gonna be just fine.

627
00:39:32,287 --> 00:39:33,370
Cuddy,

628
00:39:35,498 --> 00:39:36,665
your guilt.

629
00:39:37,667 --> 00:39:40,627
It's perverse and it makes you
a crappy doctor.

630
00:39:44,090 --> 00:39:46,467
It also makes you
okay at what you do.

631
00:39:47,385 --> 00:39:50,846
You figure a perverted sense
of guilt makes me a good boss.

632
00:39:50,972 --> 00:39:54,767
Now, would the world be a better
place if people never felt guilty?

633
00:39:54,893 --> 00:39:56,769
Makes sex better.

634
00:39:56,895 --> 00:39:59,980
You should have seen her in the
last months of our relationship.

635
00:40:00,106 --> 00:40:02,274
A lot of guilt.
A lot of screaming.

636
00:40:04,694 --> 00:40:07,863
I know this wasn't just
because it was your roof.

637
00:40:11,284 --> 00:40:12,367
Cuddy,

638
00:40:14,996 --> 00:40:19,083
you see the world as it is, and
you see the world as it could be.

639
00:40:19,209 --> 00:40:21,835
And what you don't see
is what everybody else sees,

640
00:40:22,921 --> 00:40:25,422
the giant gaping chasm
in between.

641
00:40:25,548 --> 00:40:27,508
House, I'm not naive.
I realize...

642
00:40:27,634 --> 00:40:30,177
If you did,
you never would have hired me.

643
00:40:33,807 --> 00:40:37,392
You're not happy
unless things are just right,

644
00:40:37,519 --> 00:40:39,061
which means two things.

645
00:40:39,854 --> 00:40:43,690
That you're a good boss,
and you'll never be happy.

646
00:40:48,696 --> 00:40:52,366
By the way, why does everybody
think you and I had sex?

647
00:40:53,118 --> 00:40:55,452
You think there could be
something to it?

648
00:41:05,672 --> 00:41:09,341
Cuddy feels guilty about not
diagnosing psittacosis any earlier?

649
00:41:12,011 --> 00:41:13,262
I think so.

650
00:41:14,639 --> 00:41:16,557
There's no way she could have.

651
00:41:17,225 --> 00:41:18,350
No.

652
00:41:20,353 --> 00:41:21,854
No way she could have.

653
00:41:33,116 --> 00:41:34,408
It's raining.

